1 m i n m 11111111 m 111 m m i\nTHE WHITE PASS YUKON ROUTE\nTHE ROUTE OF COMFORT, SPEED. SERVICE. SAFETY\ni During tho winter season of 1913-14 our regular train service will be maintained North and\nSouth bound between Skaguay and white Horse, every Tuesday and Friday.\nWINTER 8TAGE SERVICE\nbetween White Horse and Dawsorf will be in regular operation, affording our patrons the\nmaximum of Comfort and Safety.\nTho White P*jm Yukon Route will maintain an efficient freight and paaaenger atage aer-\nvice from White Horse, Yukon Territory, via Lake Kluane, to the\nCHISANA GOLD FIELDS\nTnia is thoonly safe and sano route to the new diggings, and we will gladly answer all In-\nq Ulrica. Wo will also oprrate a freight service up the White River, and carry a full line of\ngroceries and foed at mouth of White River, These supplies can be obtained by proepectors\nat reasonable prices, For full Information apply to\nJ. E. Dcmpscy, Traffic Manager. 612 Second Ave., Seattle. Wash.\ni H. Wheeler. Supt. Mail Service Dept. White Home, Y. T i\nii 1111 iiii iiiiiiiiniuiiniiiiiiiiiniiii\nThe Home of Hart Schaffner Marx\nCLOTHING\nSuits from M5.oo to S30?oo\nd\nAlasfca-T readwell\nGold Mining Co.\nTreadwell\nAlaska","height":"25200","width":"18426"}}
